  <section id="glossary-num" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-numeric">
    <h2 id="heading-numeric" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">#</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">2G Testing</h3>
      <p>Simulating very slow mobile networks to verify that a page remains usable.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-a" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-a">
    <h2 id="heading-a" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">A</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Abstract Syntax Tree (AST)</h3>
      <p>The internal structure created when the browser parses JavaScript code.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Analytics Script</h3>
      <p>A third-party script used to measure user behaviour and traffic.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Anti-Pattern</h3>
      <p>A design choice that appears useful but harms performance or usability in practice.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">API Design</h3>
      <p>Structuring APIs so they transfer the least possible data and process requests efficiently.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">API Response Time</h3>
      <p>The time taken for an API endpoint to return a result.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Architecture &amp; Engineering</h3>
      <p>The overall section of the framework that covers technical design decisions affecting performance and resilience.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/">Architecture &amp; Engineering</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Asset</h3>
      <p>Any downloadable page resource, including images, CSS, JavaScript, fonts, or video.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Asset Optimisation</h3>
      <p>Reducing the size and cost of website assets while preserving their usefulness.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Asynchronous Script</h3>
      <p>A JavaScript file that loads without blocking the rest of the page.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">AVIF</h3>
      <p>An advanced image format that offers even higher compression efficiency than WebP.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-b" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-b">
    <h2 id="heading-b" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">B</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Background Data Usage</h3>
      <p>Data transferred behind the scenes without direct user action.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Bandwidth</h3>
      <p>The amount of data that can be transferred over a connection per second.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Bandwidth-Aware Design</h3>
      <p>A strategy where the website adapts based on available network speed.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Battery Drain</h3>
      <p>Excessive use of power caused by inefficient scripts or animations.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Blank Screen Problem</h3>
      <p>A situation where users see nothing until JavaScript finishes loading.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Bottleneck</h3>
      <p>A part of the system that slows down overall performance.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Brotli</h3>
      <p>A more efficient compression algorithm than Gzip that often produces smaller files.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Browser Cache</h3>
      <p>Storage inside the browser used to save downloaded assets for later visits.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Build Process</h3>
      <p>The automated sequence used to generate and optimise a website before deployment.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Build Time</h3>
      <p>The stage when static pages are generated before deployment.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Bundle Analyzer</h3>
      <p>A tool used to inspect what is included inside a JavaScript bundle.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Bundle Size Budget</h3>
      <p>A fixed maximum size allowed for page assets.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Business Logic</h3>
      <p>The part of an application that contains its rules and functionality.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Bytecode</h3>
      <p>The low-level instructions created after JavaScript compilation.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-c" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-c">
    <h2 id="heading-c" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">C</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Cache Header</h3>
      <p>Metadata sent by the server that tells the browser how long content can be stored.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Cache Hit Rate</h3>
      <p>The percentage of requests served from cache instead of requiring a fresh download.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Cache Invalidation</h3>
      <p>The process of clearing or updating old cached content when it changes.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Cache-Control</h3>
      <p>A common HTTP header used to specify caching rules for assets.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">CDN Cache</h3>
      <p>Cached copies of content stored on edge servers close to users.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">CDN-Backed Website</h3>
      <p>A website that relies on a content delivery network to improve speed globally.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Client-Side Rendering (CSR)</h3>
      <p>Rendering page content in the browser using JavaScript.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Code Splitting</h3>
      <p>Dividing JavaScript into smaller files that load only when needed.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Compile Cost</h3>
      <p>The time the browser spends converting JavaScript into executable form.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Content Delivery Network (CDN)</h3>
      <p>A distributed network of servers that deliver content from the location closest to the user.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Content Delivery Optimisation</h3>
      <p>Improving how quickly and efficiently content reaches users around the world.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Content Visibility</h3>
      <p>The speed at which meaningful content becomes visible to users.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Content-Heavy Page</h3>
      <p>A page whose main purpose is to display text, data, or information rather than rich interaction.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Core Content First Strategy</h3>
      <p>Prioritising essential information before loading secondary features.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">CPU Execution Time</h3>
      <p>The amount of processing time required to execute JavaScript.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">CPU Throttling</h3>
      <p>Artificially slowing the processor during testing to simulate a low-end device.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">CPU Usage</h3>
      <p>The amount of processor power consumed by a page or script.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Critical CSS</h3>
      <p>The minimum CSS needed to display important content immediately.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Critical Resource</h3>
      <p>A resource required immediately for the page to become usable.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">CSS Bundle</h3>
      <p>A file containing one or more stylesheets combined together.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">CSS Bundle Size</h3>
      <p>The total size of CSS delivered to the browser.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">CSS Minification</h3>
      <p>Removing spaces, comments, and unnecessary characters from CSS files.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)</h3>
      <p>A measurement of how much visible content moves unexpectedly during loading.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-d" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-d">
    <h2 id="heading-d" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">D</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Data Plan Cost</h3>
      <p>The amount of money users may spend because a website consumes large amounts of mobile data.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Data Transfer Capacity</h3>
      <p>The maximum amount of data a network can carry at once.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Data Transparency</h3>
      <p>Clearly showing users when and why data is being loaded or consumed.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Deferral</h3>
      <p>Delaying non-critical scripts or assets until after important content appears.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Dependency</h3>
      <p>A library, framework, or external script required by a website.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Dependency Audit</h3>
      <p>Reviewing which external libraries are included and whether they are necessary.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Dependency Risk Assessment</h3>
      <p>Evaluating whether a third-party script is worth its performance cost.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Device Capability</h3>
      <p>The available CPU, memory, storage, and graphics performance of the user’s device.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Device Strain</h3>
      <p>Excessive use of CPU, memory, or battery that reduces performance on low-end devices.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">DNS Resolution</h3>
      <p>The process of converting a domain name into an IP address.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">DOM Manipulation</h3>
      <p>Updating or changing elements in the browser’s document structure.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">DOM Query Caching</h3>
      <p>Saving references to frequently used page elements to avoid repeated searches.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Dynamic Adaptation</h3>
      <p>Changing application behaviour automatically depending on network speed or device capability.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Dynamic Content</h3>
      <p>Content that changes or appears after the page has already loaded.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Dynamic Image Quality</h3>
      <p>Lowering image resolution automatically when bandwidth is limited.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Dynamic Import</h3>
      <p>A technique for loading a JavaScript module only when required.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-e" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-e">
    <h2 id="heading-e" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">E</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Edge Server</h3>
      <p>A server located near users that stores cached copies of content.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Efficiency Engineering</h3>
      <p>Designing systems to use the smallest amount of data, CPU, memory, and bandwidth possible.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Efficiency over Excess</h3>
      <p>The LRO principle of only delivering what is needed rather than maximising features or complexity.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Efficiency per Unit of Resource</h3>
      <p>The LRO principle of delivering maximum value while consuming minimal data, power, memory, and processing.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Efficient Data Format</h3>
      <p>A structured format that uses less bandwidth and processing.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Engineering Workflow</h3>
      <p>The sequence of measuring, optimising, testing, and validating performance changes.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Event Delegation</h3>
      <p>Attaching one listener to a parent element rather than many listeners to children.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Event Listener</h3>
      <p>A function that waits for a user action such as a click or scroll.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Execution Cost</h3>
      <p>The CPU time required to run JavaScript after it has loaded.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-f" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-f">
    <h2 id="heading-f" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">F</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Filtering</h3>
      <p>Limiting API responses so only relevant records are returned.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">First Contentful Paint (FCP)</h3>
      <p>The moment when the browser first displays text, images, or other visible content.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Font Loading</h3>
      <p>The process of downloading and applying a font to page text.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Font Subsetting</h3>
      <p>Including only the characters actually required in a font file.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Frontend Architecture</h3>
      <p>The overall structure of how a website’s user interface is built and delivered.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Frontend Resource Layer</h3>
      <p>The collection of CSS, JavaScript, fonts, and other files that control page appearance and behaviour.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-g" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-g">
    <h2 id="heading-g" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">G</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Google Lighthouse</h3>
      <p>A performance auditing tool used to evaluate page speed, accessibility, and best practices.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Gzip</h3>
      <p>A compression algorithm used to reduce the size of text files such as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-h" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-h">
    <h2 id="heading-h" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">H</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">HTML Shell</h3>
      <p>A minimal HTML structure delivered before JavaScript generates the full interface.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">HTTP Request</h3>
      <p>A browser request for a page resource such as HTML, CSS, JavaScript, or an image.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Hybrid Rendering</h3>
      <p>Combining multiple rendering strategies depending on the type of page.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Hydration</h3>
      <p>The process where JavaScript attaches interactivity to already-rendered HTML.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-i" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-i">
    <h2 id="heading-i" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">I</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Icon Font</h3>
      <p>A font file used to display icons instead of text.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Image Compression</h3>
      <p>Reducing image file size while keeping acceptable visual quality.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Incremental Static Regeneration (ISR)</h3>
      <p>Updating specific static pages in the background after deployment.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">IndexedDB</h3>
      <p>A browser-based database used for storing larger amounts of structured data offline.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Initial JS</h3>
      <p>The JavaScript required to load the page initially.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Interaction Latency</h3>
      <p>Delay between user input and visible response.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-j" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-j">
    <h2 id="heading-j" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">J</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">JavaScript Bundle</h3>
      <p>A combined file containing JavaScript code used by the page.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">JavaScript Minification</h3>
      <p>Removing unnecessary characters and shortening variable names to reduce JS file size.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">JavaScript Payload</h3>
      <p>The total amount of JavaScript transferred to the browser.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">JS Budget</h3>
      <p>A predefined limit for how much JavaScript can be delivered to the user.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">JSON</h3>
      <p>A lightweight text-based format commonly used for API responses.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-l" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-l">
    <h2 id="heading-l" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">L</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Latency</h3>
      <p>The time delay between a user action and the resulting response.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Layout Recalculation</h3>
      <p>The browser recalculating the size and position of elements after changes.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Layout Shift</h3>
      <p>A visible movement of page elements while the page is loading.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Layout Stability</h3>
      <p>Keeping elements from moving unexpectedly while a page loads.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Layout-Breaking Animation</h3>
      <p>An animation that causes visible movement or instability in the page layout.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Lazy Loading</h3>
      <p>Loading content only when it becomes necessary, such as when it scrolls into view.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Lazy-Loaded Feature</h3>
      <p>A feature that is downloaded only when the user actually needs it.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Lightweight Alternative</h3>
      <p>A smaller or simpler library used instead of a heavier dependency.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Local Data Storage</h3>
      <p>Keeping data on the user’s device rather than requiring it from the server every time.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Local Storage API</h3>
      <p>A browser feature for storing small pieces of persistent data as key-value pairs.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Long Task</h3>
      <p>A JavaScript operation that blocks the browser for an extended period.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Low Resource Optimisation (LRO)</h3>
      <p>A design and engineering approach focused on making websites usable on slow networks, low-end devices, and constrained environments.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Low-End Device</h3>
      <p>A phone, tablet, or computer with limited memory, storage, or processing power.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-m" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-m">
    <h2 id="heading-m" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">M</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Main Thread</h3>
      <p>The browser process responsible for rendering, handling input, and executing JavaScript.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Media Embedding</h3>
      <p>Adding video, audio, or interactive media to a page.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Media Payload</h3>
      <p>The total size of images, video, and audio included on a page.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Memory Leak</h3>
      <p>A bug where memory is consumed continuously and not released.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Memory Usage</h3>
      <p>The amount of RAM consumed by the website.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Mobile-First Application</h3>
      <p>An application designed primarily for phones and constrained devices before desktop.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Monolithic File</h3>
      <p>A very large JavaScript file containing too many unrelated functions.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-n" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-n">
    <h2 id="heading-n" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">N</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Native Browser API</h3>
      <p>Built-in browser functionality that avoids the need for heavy libraries.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Network Detection</h3>
      <p>Measuring or estimating the speed and quality of the current internet connection.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Network Instability</h3>
      <p>Unreliable or intermittent internet connectivity that may interrupt requests or downloads.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Network Overhead</h3>
      <p>Additional data or requests generated that do not directly contribute to the user’s immediate goal.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Non-Essential Feature</h3>
      <p>A secondary feature that can be disabled or delayed on poor connections.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Number of Requests</h3>
      <p>The count of all network requests required to load a page.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-o" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-o">
    <h2 id="heading-o" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">O</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Observability</h3>
      <p>The ability to understand the behaviour and performance of a system through monitoring.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Offline Access</h3>
      <p>The ability to use part of a website or application without an active internet connection.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Offline-First Application</h3>
      <p>An application designed to continue functioning even when the network is unavailable.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Offscreen Image</h3>
      <p>An image that is not immediately visible and can therefore be delayed.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Operational Cost</h3>
      <p>The cost of infrastructure, bandwidth, servers, and hosting required to run a system.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Over-Fetching</h3>
      <p>Requesting more information than is needed.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-p" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-p">
    <h2 id="heading-p" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">P</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Page Load Time</h3>
      <p>The total time required for a page to finish loading.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Page Weight</h3>
      <p>The combined size of all resources needed to load a page.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">PageSpeed Insights</h3>
      <p>A Google tool that analyses website performance and optimisation opportunities.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Pagination</h3>
      <p>Splitting large datasets into smaller pages to reduce request size.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Parse Cost</h3>
      <p>The time the browser spends reading and understanding JavaScript code.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Payload</h3>
      <p>The data transferred between the client and server in a request or response.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Payload Minimisation</h3>
      <p>Reducing data transfer by sending only the information needed.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Performance Baseline</h3>
      <p>The initial measurement of a website before optimisation begins.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Performance Engineering</h3>
      <p>The practice of improving how quickly and efficiently a system responds to user requests.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Performance Monitoring</h3>
      <p>Continuously measuring speed, responsiveness, and system behaviour.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Persistent Caching</h3>
      <p>Keeping files stored across browser sessions so they can be reused on future visits.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Polyfill</h3>
      <p>Additional JavaScript used to provide support for older browsers.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Processing Overhead</h3>
      <p>Extra CPU or memory cost required to perform a task beyond the essential work.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Progressive Enhancement</h3>
      <p>Building a website that works without JavaScript and then adding enhancements.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Progressive Rendering</h3>
      <p>Displaying content in layers so users see something useful as quickly as possible.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-q" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-q">
    <h2 id="heading-q" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">Q</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Query Structure</h3>
      <p>The arrangement of parameters or filters used to request data from an API.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-r" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-r">
    <h2 id="heading-r" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">R</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Rate Limiting</h3>
      <p>Restricting how frequently a user or client can make requests.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Re-Render</h3>
      <p>A repeated update of the visible interface that may be unnecessary.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Real User Monitoring (RUM)</h3>
      <p>Collecting performance data from actual users instead of laboratory tests.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Real-World Condition Testing</h3>
      <p>Testing websites on slow networks and low-end devices instead of only fast computers.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Rebuild</h3>
      <p>Re-generating a static site when content changes.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Redundant Field</h3>
      <p>An unnecessary property included in an API response.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Redundant Request</h3>
      <p>A repeated or unnecessary network request that wastes bandwidth and server resources.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Rehydration</h3>
      <p>Another term for hydration, where client-side JavaScript activates a server-rendered page.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Render-Blocking CSS</h3>
      <p>CSS that prevents content from appearing until the stylesheet loads.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Rendering Strategy</h3>
      <p>The approach used to decide where and when a page is generated.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Repeat Visit Optimisation</h3>
      <p>Improving speed for returning users by avoiding re-downloading unchanged content.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Request Count</h3>
      <p>The total number of files or API calls required to load a page.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Reserved Space</h3>
      <p>Empty space intentionally allocated so media can load without moving the layout.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Resilience</h3>
      <p>The ability of a system to remain usable even when conditions are poor or components fail.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Resource Failure Tolerance</h3>
      <p>Designing pages so they remain usable even if some assets fail to load.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Resource-Constrained Environment</h3>
      <p>A context where users have limited bandwidth, low-end devices, unstable electricity, or expensive mobile data.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Response Time</h3>
      <p>The total time taken for a request to be processed and returned to the user.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Responsive Image</h3>
      <p>An image that changes size or quality depending on the user’s screen and bandwidth.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Reuse over Recompute</h3>
      <p>An LRO principle that encourages caching and reusing data instead of recalculating or reloading it.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Round Trip</h3>
      <p>A complete cycle where the browser sends a request and waits for a server response.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Round-Trip Reduction</h3>
      <p>Reducing the number of requests between browser and server to improve speed.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Route Rule</h3>
      <p>A rule that determines which rendering strategy should be used for a given page.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Runtime Rendering</h3>
      <p>Rendering performed while the user is actively requesting the page.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-s" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-s">
    <h2 id="heading-s" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">S</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Scalability</h3>
      <p>A system’s ability to continue performing well when the number of users or requests increases.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Search Engine Optimisation (SEO)</h3>
      <p>The process of making content easier for search engines to discover and rank.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">SEO-Friendly</h3>
      <p>Easy for search engines to understand and index.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Server Load</h3>
      <p>The amount of work a backend server must perform to handle requests.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Server Response Time</h3>
      <p>The amount of time a server takes to start responding to a request.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Server-Side Cache</h3>
      <p>Temporary storage on the server used to avoid recomputing or regenerating content repeatedly.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Server-Side Rendering (SSR)</h3>
      <p>Rendering page HTML on the server before sending it to the browser.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Single Page Application (SPA)</h3>
      <p>A website where most navigation and rendering happen inside one JavaScript-driven page.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Smallest Possible Payload</h3>
      <p>The LRO principle of transferring only the minimum necessary amount of data.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Static Delivery</h3>
      <p>Delivering pages directly from storage or a CDN without server-side computation.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Static HTML</h3>
      <p>HTML files that are pre-generated and do not require a server to create them on demand.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Static Site Generation (SSG)</h3>
      <p>Generating pages as static HTML during a build process before deployment.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Storage Limit</h3>
      <p>The maximum amount of data a browser allows an application to store locally.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">SVG Icon</h3>
      <p>A vector-based icon that is usually smaller and more efficient than an icon font.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Synthetic Testing</h3>
      <p>Performance testing performed in controlled conditions rather than by real users.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">System Font</h3>
      <p>A font already available on the user’s device that does not require downloading.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-t" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-t">
    <h2 id="heading-t" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">T</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Targeted Optimisation</h3>
      <p>Applying improvements specifically to the components causing the largest problems.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Third-Party Dependency Optimisation</h3>
      <p>The process of reducing or replacing external libraries to lower page weight.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Third-Party JS Budget</h3>
      <p>The maximum amount of JavaScript allowed from external services.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Third-Party Script</h3>
      <p>JavaScript loaded from an external service such as analytics or advertising.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Throughput</h3>
      <p>The amount of work or number of requests a system can process in a period of time.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Time to First Byte (TTFB)</h3>
      <p>The time before the first byte of a server response reaches the browser.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Time to First Text (TTFT)</h3>
      <p>The time before readable text first appears on screen.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Time to Interactive (TTI)</h3>
      <p>The point when the page becomes responsive and usable.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Total Blocking Time (TBT)</h3>
      <p>The total time when the browser is blocked by long tasks and cannot respond to the user.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/rendering-strategies/">Rendering Strategies and LRO Impact</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Total Page Size</h3>
      <p>The total size of all assets downloaded for a page.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Tree Shaking</h3>
      <p>Removing code that is imported but never used.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-u" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-u">
    <h2 id="heading-u" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">U</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">UI Rendering</h3>
      <p>The process of drawing the visible interface in the browser.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Under-Fetching</h3>
      <p>Requiring multiple requests because the original response lacked required information.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Unused Code</h3>
      <p>CSS or JavaScript that is shipped to users but never actually used.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Unused Style</h3>
      <p>CSS that is never applied to any visible element.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">User Preference Storage</h3>
      <p>Saving settings such as theme or language locally to avoid repeated server requests.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-v" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-v">
    <h2 id="heading-v" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">V</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Validation</h3>
      <p>Confirming that an optimisation actually improved performance in real conditions.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Vendor Code</h3>
      <p>Third-party JavaScript libraries included in a project.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Video Embedding Strategy</h3>
      <p>A plan for including videos without causing excessive data use.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Visual Complexity</h3>
      <p>The amount of styling, media, and interaction included in a page.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-w" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-w">
    <h2 id="heading-w" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">W</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Web Font</h3>
      <p>A downloadable font loaded from the web.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/">Rendering &amp; Frontend Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">WebP</h3>
      <p>A modern image format designed to provide smaller file sizes than JPEG or PNG.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Webpack Performance Hints</h3>
      <p>Build-time warnings or errors when asset sizes exceed defined limits.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/frontend/javascript-usage/">JavaScript Usage Strategy</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">WebPageTest</h3>
      <p>A website testing service used to measure loading behaviour under different conditions.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">Website Technical Optimisation</h3>
      <p>Improving the technical delivery of a website to reduce size, requests, and rendering cost.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

  <section id="glossary-x" class="vf-u-margin__top--700" aria-labelledby="heading-x">
    <h2 id="heading-x" class="vf-u-type__text-heading--2" tabindex="-1">X</h2>
    <article class="vf-u-margin__top--500">
      <h3 class="vf-u-type__text-heading--3">XML</h3>
      <p>An older and often larger data format that usually consumes more bandwidth than JSON.</p>
      <p class="vf-u-margin__top--200"><a class="vf-link" href="/web-optimisation-framework/system-architecture/system-design-optimisation/">System design and optimisation</a></p>
    </article>

  </section>

</article>
